Package cmput301.f13t01.elasticsearch

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ElasticSearchResponse<T>
    A class to define the form of an ElasticSearch query response.
    ElasticSearchSearchResponse<T>
    A class allowing for the organization of objects received from the server.
    ESClient
    This class deals with all direct interaction with the server via ElasticSearch.
    ESManager
    This class is designed to interact with stored stories on ElasticSearch.
    Hits<T>
    The container for all the different responses received from the server when multiple objects have been queried.
    MediaResource
    This is a class to keep track of the identifier/location of a Media object of a given type, so that its location on the server and/or in the file hierarchy can be known.
    SearchManager
    Composes the query String to be sent to ESClient.
    StoryResource
    This class keeps track of the MediaResource objects associated with a given story so that the locations of Media objects on the server can be known.
